description:
Polish & Slavic Federal Credit Union is committed to supporting our employees’ overall wellbeing by providing valuable benefits. The credit union proudly offers a competitive benefits package, that includes: Medical, Vision and Dental Insurance, Retirement Plans, Life Insurance Plans, Tuition Reimbursement and Pet Insurance, among other benefits. We also have a generous Paid Time Off policy including Vacation, Personal and Sick Time, as well as, a Birthday Day off.




**Core Responsibilities:**



* Represent the Credit Union to the members in a courteous and professional manner and provide prompt, efficient and accurate service;


* Develop and maintain an understanding of the Credit Union philosophy, organization, bylaws and operational procedures;


* Provide general and specific service-related information concerning Credit Union products, services or policies, in person and /or by telephone;


* Respond to members’ requests, problems, and complaints, and/or direct members to the proper person/department for specific information and assistance;


* Responsible for appropriate handling of member mail and incoming documentation as well as other incoming mail;


* Develop good relationships with PSFCU vendors;


* Attend, represent and actively participate in PSFCU community events as well as actively participating in branch sponsored events;


* As per PSFCU Policy and Procedures perform routine transactions, including but not limited to:


* opening/closing accounts and shares;
* accepting wire transfer requests-domestic and international;
* performing change of address, issuing temporary checks;
* performing Harland Clarke share drafts orders;
* processing ATM card and Debit card requests;
* handling and processing IRA accounts;
* handling and processing Share Certificates of Deposits;
* handling and processing Club accounts;
* direct deposit of Social Security and payroll checks to members accounts;
* processing lost passbook requests;
* performing Chex Systems checks;
* set up and provide access to On-Line Banking, Mobile Banking
* Service existing accounts; set up new accounts files and provide members with all necessary information and assistance;


* Provide members with information regarding consumer loans, business loans, and VISA cards and appropriately align the right loan product for the member’s financing need;


* Assist members in the completion of the loan application (real estate loans excluded) and all associated forms;


* Accept and process loan applications of all types (real estate loans excluded); review documentation for accuracy; and request all necessary documentation required to complete the loan application;


* Notify members by phone or mail that their checkbooks are ready for pickup at the branch;


* Conduct orientation interview on Credit Union services and programs with each new Credit Union member;


* Effectively offer Credit Union products and services through the practice of established sales and service techniques;


* Post dividends prior to the end of the month for all closed member accounts;


* Perform all functions of Teller when business needs dictate;


* Maintain extensive knowledge of all products and services;


* Monitor changes in interest rates and effectively communicate pricing to members


* Maintain superior knowledge and full understanding of consumer loan products;


* Act as a Safe Deposit Box Attendant, responsible for handling box rentals, providing access to the vault area and related functions;


* Perform other duties or responsibilities as assigned;


* Effectively cross-sell PSFCU products and services in order to achieve Branch Goals as per the Branch Goals Incentive Plan.


* Travel to and cover at other branches if necessary and needed.


* And other functions as needed and delegated by the Branch Manager;



**Requirements:**


* 1-2 years of work experience;
* 1 year of experience as a Teller;
* Basic computer skills and knowledge of computer software programs;
* Ability to cross sell products;
* Fluency in spoken and written Polish and English
* High School Diploma


Pay: $16.20 - $22.26 per hour



AN EQUAL OPPORTUNITY EMPLOYER

#### **Education**


Required* High School or better

Sethi and Mazaheri LLC, a boutique immigration law firm with a strong commitment to social justice, is seeking a full-time Paralegal/Case Coordinator. We are looking for a professional comfortable in a dynamic environment who can work well as part of a team in a fast-paced, deadline-driven office. The ability to multitask and comfortably communicate with clients and government agencies is important. Experience in an immigration law firm is required with talent based (EB/O/P visa) familiarity preferred, and the ideal candidate possessing a thorough understanding of general immigration processes and how they interact/intersect.

**General Duties:**

In this role, you will collaborate with attorneys and staff in legal document preparation and be responsible for communication with clients and contractors, as well as providing oversight in the filing of immigration benefits. Additionally, you will be charged with the general office administration tasks necessary to file submissions, such as compilation and mailing. The specific duties in this role are dependent upon the needs of the law firm and may be subject to change.

**Specific Duties:**

* Tracking and managing critical deadlines firmwide and providing oversight on case progress within docket areas;
* Coordinating with clients, contractors, and legal team to maintain deadlines and file cases in a timely manner;
* Maintaining and overseeing an active docket across practice areas, including family-based, consular, removal, employment-based, asylum, and other immigration case types;
* Providing initial review and feedback to paralegals and contractors on standard applications, including but not limited to, I-765s, I-131s, I-90s, FOIAs, etc.;
* Supervising individual work on cases to ensure that submissions meet the standards of the firm, including the review of final packets within certain areas of practice;
* Participating in case meetings with attorneys to determine case issues and plan case strategy;
* Communicating with clients, labor/management organizations, and contractors regularly;
* Performing client intake, including gathering supporting documents, completing forms, and preparing legal memos;
* Preparing and assembling petitions for the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services, U.S. Embassies and Consulates, Labor/Management organizations, and Federal courts, as needed; and,
* Administrative tasks, such as mailing, scanning, copying, calendaring deadlines, scheduling meetings, maintaining files, and other related duties.

**Position Requirements:** 

* Prior experience in an immigration law firm;
* Bachelor or Associate degree;
* Proficiency with Microsoft Office and Adobe Acrobat programs;
* Strong proofreading skills;
* Demonstrable expertise in writing;
* Clear and effective communication skills; and,
* Excellent time-management and organizational skills, including attention to detail.

**Qualities of an Ideal Candidate:** 

* Minimum 3 years experience in an immigration law firm;
* Fluency in a second language;
* Prior experience with EB/O/P cases;
* Determined worker with attention to detail and the ability to multitask;
* Leadership skills and a team player attitude;
* Strong organizational and research skills; and,
* Experience and/or familiarity with art and entertainment.

**What we offer:** 

* Medical insurance;
* Paid Time Off;
* Vacation;
* Retirement Plan;
* Opportunity for growth; and,
* A positive team environment that encourages employees to evolve and flourish in their role.

**Employment Details:**

* Full-time
* In-person
* Pay: $60k - $64k
* Contact: info@sethimaz.com

**About Sethi and Mazaheri LLC** 

Sethi & Mazaheri LLC is composed of a group of social justice-minded attorneys with enthusiasm, empathy, and expertise. We are dedicated to helping people who are in need of getting or maintaining legal status in the United States and might otherwise be denied access to the country. We aim to provide our legal services with high quality, precision, and efficiency. Our lawyers can assist with all types of immigration legal affairs, including green cards, citizenship, asylum, talent and employment-based visas, and deportation and removal defense, among other personalized legal issues.

Job Type: Full-time

Pay: From $60,000.00 per year

Benefits:

* 401(k)
* 401(k) matching
* Health insurance
* Paid sick time
* Paid time off

Schedule:

* 8 hour shift
* Monday to Friday

Education:

* Bachelor's (Preferred)

Experience:

* Immigration Paralegal: 2 years (Required)

Ability to Commute:

* Jersey City, NJ 07302 (Required)

Work Location: In person
